&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Location&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;: We are flexible! Come and join us either in Hamburg, Berlin or Barcelona.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Freenow by Lyft empowers smarter mobility decisions helping people to move freely and cities to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking a talented Analytics Engineer (m/f/d) to join our Data Team and collaborate with Data Analysts, Developers, and Data Scientists, in implementing a Data Mesh architecture that will enable our domains to access trusted data to unlock business opportunities easily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine empowering teams with the data they need to make game-changing decisions. Data puzzles excite you? Do you thrive in a collaborative environment where you can shape the future of data infrastructure? If so, we want you!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be ready to work in a multinational, diverse, highly motivated, and collaborative team of passionate data professionals who strive for excellence and like to have fun.&amp;nbsp; Are you ready for your next ride?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR DAILY ADVENTURES WILL INCLUDE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing expertise and collaborating with stakeholders to develop new data products and improve on existing ones in a Data Mesh environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously engaging with data analysts, data scientists, and software engineers to gain an understanding of the problems that need to be solved, gathering requirements, and defining the best deliverables to match the business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working hand-in-hand with developers to create and capture data that aligns with business logic, enabling powerful modeling and analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the quality, availability, and trustworthiness of data by applying data quality checks and data contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing data analysis to troubleshoot data-related issues and assist in resolving them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing, building and maintaining the definitive source of truth for KPIs, empowering strategic decisions across all domains&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working towards the creation of an environment where self-service capabilities are available and data can be accessible by everyone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Tech Tools&lt;/strong&gt;: SQL | Python | Databricks | Tableau | Mixpanel | Airflow | AWS | Kafka | Debezium&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TO BE SUCCESSFUL IN THIS ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You &lt;strong&gt;have curiosity in your essence, &lt;/strong&gt;aligned with attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in working in a data-driven analytics environment, preferably within tech product organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expert level of SQL&lt;/strong&gt; (especially SparkSQL) and experience in building data pipelines is a core requirement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have good knowledge of at least one programming language and are happy to learn more. Our core language is Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional analytical skills&lt;/strong&gt;, lateral thinking, and proven experience in solving highly challenging problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience in working with data visualization tools&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g.Tableau, Qlikview) and event tracking (e.g. Mixpanel, Google Analytics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent English communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with AWS, Hive, Spark, Trino, Databricks, and Airflow is helpful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
