&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as primary People Business Partner to the European Leadership Team and team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business strategy into people, organizational, and talent priorities that drive performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align European people strategy with Lyft’s global People strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape workforce planning and operating model decisions to support growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transformation, Growth &amp;amp; M&amp;amp;A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead people strategy for organizational transformation and business evolution across Europe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own European people integration in partnership with Global People M&amp;amp;A and partner with cross functional partners on diligence and integration efforts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive organizational design and change initiatives to enable scalable growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead critical integration phases, including temporary oversight of HR Operations where required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talent, Leadership &amp;amp; Culture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
